</para><para depth="0">C:\Program Files\Google\Google SketchUp 6\Components\People

</para><para depth="0">...and double-click one of the '.skp' model files. This should cause
Windows to open SketchUp, instead of you starting SketchUp by using a
shortcut.
_________

</para><para depth="0">I've seen this problem reported before, but only for Vista (never XP.)
So, I can't be certain that this will work.

</para><para depth="0">If it works, the first thing you should do is go to...

</para><para depth="0">'Window &gt; Preferences &gt; OpenGL'

</para><para depth="0">...and disable 'Use hardware acceleration'

</para><para depth="0">Also, close the 'Learning Center' and 'Instructor' windows.

</para><para depth="0">Now close SketchUp and see if it will now open from a shortcut.
________

</para><para depth="0">Check to ensure that your graphics card and driver are compatible with
SketchUp (the rest of your system looks okay):

</para><para depth="0"><url>http://sketchup.google.com/support/bin/answer.py?answer=36208</url>
________
Regards,
Taff

